  "datePublished": "2026-03-03",
  "description": "Autopoiesis (from the Greek auto, self, and poiesis, making or production) is a concept introduced by Chilean biologists Humberto Maturana and Francisco Varela to characterize the organization of living systems. An autopoietic system is one that continuously produces the components and processes that constitute it: it makes itself. The system\u0026rsquo;s organization (the relations between components) is invariant, but its structure (the specific components) is continuously replaced through the system\u0026rsquo;s own activity.\n",
  "name": "Autopoiesis",
